column5: How much would you pay for a discontinued spoon?  Somebody just dropped $44.17 + $10 shipping on EBAY for a Delfin Aligator(new in package).  Wow.  It's a great spoon and it does have a cult following with brookie fishermen, but who would've expected that type of money?!?  Check your spoon/pier-chucking boxes for buried treasure!

Too funny...I picked one up new in the package about eight years ago for $5, at an antique, used store in Cambridge.  They work really well for Huron rainbow off the piers, but, for that money, I can buy an awfull lot of little Cleos that work almost, if not, as well.
Not surprised. Saw a guy drop 888 on a Bagleys rare blue crankbait on ebay link to listing  I'd dare to say some people are a bit  but I won't judge least I be judged too. lol
Yikes that muck for an antique lure? WOW
I'd have to count but I think I likely have a dozen or more of the Aligators all slightly used, great lures Richard
